"n. 尸体 【英】 n. 尸体(a dead body; corpse) 【记】 cad(倒下=fall)+aver →倒下的人→尸体 【同】 同根词: decadent(堕落的); cadence(节奏) n. 尸体(尤指有待于解剖的躯体) = corpse 【记】cad = fall倒下－倒下的人－尸体cad无赖, aver断言－无赖说的话不能算数－象死人的话一样. Cad = cab出租车, a一, ver读: 味儿: 出租车里有一股味道－谋杀完别人就可以把他扔到出租车里, 所以这是死尸味道. 【参】decadent(adj 颓废的); cadence(n 节奏) 【记】源自cadere 倒下；音：开打卧，一开始打仗就卧倒成了死人； cadaver (n.)  c.1500, from Latin cadaver ""dead body (of men or animals),"" probably from a perfective participle of cadere ""to fall, sink, settle down, decline, perish"" (see case (n.1)). Compare Greek ptoma ""dead body,"" literally ""a fall"" (see ptomaine); poetic English the fallen ""those who died in battle."""
